JOHANNESBURG The South African National Defence Force (SANDF) is expected to release a report to Ekurhuleni Metropolitan Municipality on the possibility of resuming rescue operations for the five-year-old boy who fell into a deep disused mine shaft near Boksburg.Richard Thole fell down the shaft in the informal settlement known as Jerusalem on Saturday, 25 February, 2017.READ: Hope fades as boy remains trapped in mineEkurhuleni Metropolitan Municipality spokesperson, Gugu Ndima, on Tuesday said the SANDF was expected to release its report tomorrow , which will give details of the next steps to be taken.SANDF was deployed to assist emergency services last week with rescue operations into the 100m deep shaft. But shortly after that the rescue operations had to be halted because the ground was unstable and was later worsened by the heavy rains.African News Agency